From: OpenAI Codex <codex@openai.com>
Subject: [PATCH] net: ethernet: freescale: dpaa: add Goal 1 flowtable executor

Add the first Goal 1 DPAA execution tier on top of the compiled-flow base:

- index installed flows by exact ingress tuple for runtime lookup
- forward accepted packets through a fresh skb path instead of mutating
  and reinjecting the original ingress skb
- execute precompiled Ethernet rewrite, TTL or hop-limit decrement, and
  exact IPv4 NAT when present in the compiled rule
- expose delayed hit and fallback counters through the existing sysfs
  visibility

This stays within the stock Linux flowtable object, keeps VLAN and PPPoE
execution out of Goal 1, and leaves true FMAN-resident forwarding for
the later Goal 2 series.

